Clarified branch direction:

- `context` and `compost` should not be first-class core CLI features
- they also are not purely maintainer-internal workflow
- they belong in the user-facing agent workflow layer taught by `SKILL.md`
- that workflow layer can include repo-shipped scripts (`context-workflow.sh`, `path-history.sh`, `note-history.sh`, `compost-workflow.sh`)

So the intended layering is:
1. thin core CLI primitives
2. skill/workflow layer for richer agent behavior
3. maintainer-only repo-development discipline kept separate from user surfaces

This keeps the product surface coherent for external users while still giving full-checkout agents ergonomic workflows.
